docs.abstract: The 5-to-4 ruling, issued in the middle of the night, provided a rare glimpse of the inner workings of a court bitterly divided on the death penalty.
docs.snippet: The 5-to-4 ruling, issued in the middle of the night, provided a rare glimpse of the inner workings of a court bitterly divided on the death penalty.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The dissent, tinged with anguish and filled with bitter accusations, was not ready until almost 3 a.m. It described a rupture in the carefully tended norms of civility at the Supreme Court. And it provided a rare glimpse into ordinarily secret deliberations.

docs.abstract: The justices must decide if a law that forbids employment discrimination based on sex also bars discrimination based on sexual orientation or transgender status.
docs.snippet: The justices must decide if a law that forbids employment discrimination based on sex also bars discrimination based on sexual orientation or transgender status.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Supreme Court announced on Monday that it would decide whether the Civil Rights Act of 1964 guarantees protections from workplace discrimination to gay and transgender people in three cases expected to provide the first indication of how the court’s new conservative majority will approach L.G.B.T. rights.

headline.main: Supreme Court to Decide Whether Landmark Civil Rights Law Applies to Gay and Transgender Workers
headline.print_headline: Justices to Weigh Wider View of Sex Bias Law
